message.text:
BREAKING: Per recommendation of the Manila DRRM Office, IN PERSON or FACE-TO-FACE afternoon classes in ALL LEVELS for both public and private are suspended due to the volcanic sulfuric dioxide emission from Taal Volcano.

Work in the city government of Manila, including its satellite offices, is likewise suspended starting 1:00PM.

However, agencies whose functions involve the delivery of basic and health services, preparedness/response to disaster and calamities, and/or the performance of other vital services shall continue with their operations and render the necessary services.

The public is advised to continue wearing face masks and to limit outdoor activities when possible.

#WalangPasok

message.text:
WALANG PASOK: As of 11:30AM, tinaas na ng PAG ASA ang Signal no 1 sa Metro Manila dahil sa Bagyong #KristinePH. 

Alinsunod sa Department of Education Order No. 37, Series of 2022, AUTOMATIC na SUSPENDED ang klase sa Kinder hanggang Senior High School sa lahat ng paaralan, pampubliko at pribado, kasama ONLINE CLASSES, kasama ang mga nasa Alternative Learning System (ALS) sa Pamahalaang Lungsod ng Maynila ngayon HAPON. 

Manatili na lang po sa inyong mga tahanan at inaabisuhan ang lahat na mag handa at mag ingat.

#WalangPasok
